<p> ARTS is a fully automated method for aligning a pair of
nucleic
acid 3D structures (RNAs or DNAs) and detecting a-priori unknown
common substructures. The identified common substructures can be
either large global folds containing hundreds and even thousands of
nucleotides or small local tertiary motifs with at least two
successive base pairs. <br>

</p>

<p> ARTS is highly-efficient and can be used to search 3D
databases given a query structure. Recently, ARTS was used to construct
the<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span><a href="http://bioinfo3d.cs.tau.ac.il/DARTS/">DARTS</a>&nbsp;classification
database&nbsp;of all solved RNA 3D structures.
</p>

<p></p>

